### 3.7 Emergency Pause Procedures

```solidity
// Emergency pause function call (via Gnosis Safe or direct if EOA)

// 1. Pause CompliantStableCoin
CompliantStableCoin.pause()

// 2. RiskRegistry uses OZ Pausable
RiskRegistry.pause()

// 3. ComplianceEngine uses OZ Pausable
ComplianceEngine.pause()

// 4. FidesCompliance uses OZ Pausable
FidesCompliance.pause()

// 5. QuarantineVault uses custom emergency pause (NOT OZ Pausable)
QuarantineVault.emergencyPause()

// 6. Revoke all roles from compromised address (if applicable)
// For each contract:
contract.revokeRole(ORACLE_ROLE, compromisedAddress)
contract.revokeRole(ADMIN_ROLE, compromisedAddress)
contract.revokeRole(OPERATOR_ROLE, compromisedAddress)
contract.revokeRole(MINTER_ROLE, compromisedAddress)
contract.revokeRole(BURNER_ROLE, compromisedAddress)
contract.revokeRole(PAUSER_ROLE, compromisedAddress)
contract.revokeRole(RELEASE_ROLE, compromisedAddress)
contract.revokeRole(EMERGENCY_ROLE, compromisedAddress)

// 7. If DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE compromised, must transfer to new admin
// For each contract:
contract.grantRole(DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE, newAdminAddress)
contract.revokeRole(DEFAULT_ADMIN_ROLE, compromisedAddress)

// 8. Unpause after remediation (note: QuarantineVault uses emergencyUnpause)
CompliantStableCoin.unpause()
RiskRegistry.unpause()
ComplianceEngine.unpause()
FidesCompliance.unpause()
QuarantineVault.emergencyUnpause()
```

